Date: Mon, 29 Nov 2010 13:42:16 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 03/38] WRHV: Export wr_vb_control/status

Since IRQ enable/disable interfaces are paravirtualized by several
macros which need access wr_vb_control/status, so export them so that
modules can access them.

Signed-off-by: Yang Shi <yang.shi@windriver.com>
---
 kernel/vbi/lib.c |    3 +++
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/vbi/lib.c b/kernel/vbi/lib.c
index 9cf2e15..7b75425 100644
--- a/kernel/vbi/lib.c
+++ b/kernel/vbi/lib.c
@@ -113,6 +113,9 @@ struct vb_control *wr_vb_control;/* The address of the core's Control area */
 
 struct vb_status *wr_vb_status;	/* The address of the core's Status area */
 
+EXPORT_SYMBOL(wr_vb_control);
+EXPORT_SYMBOL(wr_vb_status);
+
 int32_t wr_irq_nested; /* Used by VBI interrupt/exception management */
  
